results.deck: Developer and publisher based in Poland.
results.description:
Techland began as a distributor in 1991. Company translated and dealt primary in educational software. Games came few years later, when Techland started making their product, as well as publishing that made by other developers. Speedway Manager was a first game made by the internal studio, which at the time contained whole one person. Without much success, company continued to produce games, mostly mediocre family software. Year 2000 was a breakthrough for Techland, marked with a release of Crime Cities, highly praised action game set in future. It was also a first game to be released outside Poland.
 
2003 was another good year for Techland. Company released Chrome - futuristic shooter made with their own game-engine entitled Chrome Engine. This engine will be a base for almost all future games made by Polish company. A period of stagnation was once again disrupted in 2006, with Call of Juarez. Not only was it first game ever to use DirectX 10, but also first Polish game to be released for Xbox 360. 1.5 millions copies of the games were sold, and this huge intake of money allowed Techland to hire more developers. In the following years company also started a copy of well-known aggregates, called BazaRecenzcji. This project was aimed at Polish users and the website was closed three years later, in 2011.
 
Earlier, in 2009, Techland released prequel to Call of Juarez - Bound in Blood. It was a first Polish title to be released for PC, Xbox 360 and PlayStation 3. But Techland was already thinking about something bigger - Dead Island. This games was originally set to debut in 2008, but was set back multiple times. Development was taking more and more resources and games such as Chrome 2 and Warhound were suspended. Finally, in September 2011 Dead Island was released, followed by big marketing campaign with famous trailer made by Axis Productions. Despite many bug, game was well received and eventually shipped 4 million copies.
